replies.body:
you are totally right, and if i was that leo i would appreciate being reminded in such a polite way.... however i have never been "asked" polity to build something by and large... and what about the flip side of that coin? what if they suggest something silly and i dont know better so i build it.... what if a lot of people want something....

what if mid was destroyed by a lux and mid wants me to build {{item:3222}} 
bot has no kills yet but rly nice farm bot wants me to build {{item:3050}} 
top is going against a autoattacking freak and wants that {{item:3110}} 

well i need my gold item.... and a sightstone.... boots would be nice

hummm.... am i playing the game, or is my team telling me how to play.... by when do you think i have the gold for everything... why do people not act the same way with any other role? its the support who people feel they get to tell how to play, what champ to play, and what to build

im not meaning to sound confrontational, i agree with what you are saying.... i would prefer though to be left alone since i do not encounter polite people often in this game and a suggestion more often than not comes out as a dictation

